quick_reads.title: 25 Most Common Web Developer Interview Questions And Answers [2020]
quick_reads.author: blog.codegiant.io
quick_reads.summary: The document provides insights into common web developer interview questions and offers guidance on how to approach them. It emphasizes the importance of communication skills, enthusiasm, and a willingness to continuously learn and improve. The questions range from introductory ones about coding experience and favorite projects to more technical inquiries about coding methodologies, languages, and problem-solving skills. Behavioral questions focusing on transparency, enthusiasm, and learning from past mistakes are also covered, along with tips on how to impress interviewers by showing a genuine interest in the company and its projects. Additionally, the document delves into technical questions related to coding practices, languages, and algorithms that may be encountered during web developer interviews.

quick_reads.title: Sunderland vs Newcastle – a fundamentally different derby eight years after the last
quick_reads.author: Chris Waugh
quick_reads.summary: Since the last meeting between Newcastle United and Sunderland almost eight years ago, both clubs have experienced significant changes, including relegations, takeovers, and reinvention. Sunderland has dominated the rivalry, remaining unbeaten in nine meetings since 2011. However, their success has been balanced by their decline, currently sitting in sixth place in the Championship. The upcoming FA Cup third-round tie between the two teams will test Sunderland against a recently successful Newcastle side. Fans and writers from both clubs express differing opinions on the significance of the rivalry and the impact of recent ownership changes.

favorite_sources.title: Have We Reached the End of TikTok’s Infinite Scroll?
favorite_sources.author: https://www.nytimes.com/by/jon-caramanica
favorite_sources.summary: TikTok's infinite scroll feature, which was once a source of endless charm and cultural discovery, is now feeling finite and crowded. The arrival of TikTok's shopping platform has turned the app into an unruly marketplace, diminishing its connection to organic music discovery and making it more challenging to create monoculture. The personalization algorithm that drives users deeper into their own taste has become a liability, leaving users wondering how a format designed for infinite scroll has become so limited. The app's emphasis on monetization and sponsored content has also dampened the overall experience. Additionally, the de-emphasis on music and the lack of evolution in optimal content form pose further challenges for TikTok's future.

recent_favorites.title: The Pulse #76: Why are layoffs coming hard and fast, again?
recent_favorites.author: Gergely Orosz
recent_favorites.summary: The Pulse #76 discusses several topics, including the recurrence of layoffs in the tech industry, Salesforce's hiring and firing practices, the challenges faced by developer platforms, and the Rabbit AI companion as a potential smartphone replacement. The article highlights how profits have become more important and layoffs are being used to boost them. It also explores the behavior of companies like Salesforce, which seem to be driven by quarterly results rather than long-term strategies. Additionally, it mentions the difficulties faced by developer platforms and the competition they face from AI startups. The article concludes with a comparison of profitability between Salesforce and other Big Tech companies.
